<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF7014B63A5F1A991898922" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF7014B63A5F1A991898922" blockId="21.[151,760,425,512]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B63A5F1A992678AE2" bold="true" box="[151,278,425,448]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Comments.</emphasis>
Based on photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF7014B6173F1A991EE8AE2" box="[577,671,425,448]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B6194F1A9921D8AC2" authorityName="Medvedev" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acroxena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="samoderzhenkovi">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B6194F1A9921D8AC2" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Acroxena samoderzhenkovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a typical representative of the 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B618EF1C993B38922" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Acroxena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B618EF1C993B38922" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">T. nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group and thus is transferred here to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B614DF1E991808922" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[639,753,489,512]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B614DF1E991808922" box="[639,753,489,512]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
